Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 3/20/99


DPI development
  Continue to work on the DPI code for the upcoming NAB show.

  There are a couple of fixes that I need on the statmux in order to have
  a smooth and reliable DPI demonstration.  The first problem is that DPI
  requires a longer delay in the statmux in order to absorb the picture
  arrival jitter due to channel alignment at splice point.  The statmux
  fails when the delay is larger than 32 pictures.  Matt has helped me
  to fix this problem.

  The other problem that statmux has is that it will stop processing pictures
  at some unknown case, which in turn cause the DPI code to die.  I have been
  working with Sangeeta and Matt to have this problem solved.

  On the demux size, I have fixed a problem which caused the code to die when
  the ad server died in the middle of an ad.  Now the code will return to
  the network feed once it notices that the ad has stopped.

  I also found that SeaChange's Ads have bad DTS at the last anchor picture.
  This is probably due to problem of the encoder that SeaChange used to
  generate its ads.  This may cause picture jumps at the splice point.
  The latest DPI code fixes bad DTS.

  I integrated Wayne's new audio package into the DPI code.



Helped Xiaoxiao to use the DPI code to debug the new FPGA code.
Several of us have noticed that the new FPGA code has the problem of
dropping packets.  The DPI code can detect this by monitoring the
continuity counter of each PID streams at the demux DSP input.
I have been told that the bug has been fixed, but have no time to
test it yet.


